{"cursor":"2461","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{| class=\"infobox\" width=\"400px\"\n|--\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#ddd;font-size:larger;text-align:center;\" |\n! Montana Synod (ELCA)\n|--\n| colspan=\"2\" |\n|--\n! Bishop:\n| Rev. Jessica Crist\n|--\n! Affiliation:\n| Evangelical Lutheran Church in America Region 1\n|--\n! s:\n| 144\n|--\n! Members:\n| 49,576 {{cite web title =Jessica Crist Elected Bishop of ELCA Montana\n| Synod publisher = ELCA News Service date = 2007-06-05 url =\n| http://www.elca.org/ScriptLib/CO/ELCA_News/encArticleList.asp?article=3605\n| accessdate = 2007-07-16 }}\n|--\n! Mailing Address:\n| 2415 13th Avenue South Great Falls, MT 59405\n|--\n! Official Website:\n| http://www.montanasynod.org/ }\nThe 'Montana Synod (ELCA)' is a [[synod#Lutheran usage|synod]], or diocese, of\nthe Evangelical Lutheran Church in America (ELCA). It encompasses state of\nMontana and four churches in Wyoming and supports congregational mission\nthroughout the region.\n\nThe Rev. Jessica Crist was elected Bishop of the Montana Synod in 2007. Crist is\nthe first female bishop in the Montana Synod, ELCA. Crist succeeded the Rev.\nRichard R. Omland, who had served the synod as bishop since 2001. Omland did not\nseek reelection. She also serves as an officer of the synod council which is the\ngoverning body of the synod between assemblies. It is composed of the Bishop and\n20 members elected at-large as well as from each of the 12 synodical geographic\nregions called clusters. There are one-hundred and forty nine Lutheran\ncongregations in the synod. {{cite web\n  | title =About Us publisher = Montana Synod ELCA date = 2007 url =\n  | http://www.montanasynod.org/AboutUs.html accessdate = 2007-05-28 }}\n\n\nThe ELCA has partnered its synods with other regions throughout the world and\nthe companion synod for Montana is the Evangelical Lutheran Church in Southern\nAfrica (ELCSA) â Cape Orange Diocese. {{cite web\n  | title = Synodical Relations publisher = Evangelical Lutheran Church in\n  | America date = 2007 url = http://www.elca.org/synods/regions.and.synods.html\n  | accessdate = 2007-05-28 }}\n\n","linknr":97,"url":"Montana_Synod_(ELCA)","recorded":1375069210,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Montana_Synod_(ELCA)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Montana_Synod_(ELCA)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Mt-synod-elca-logo.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/e/e5/Mt-synod-elca-logo.jpg","/wiki/Bishop","/wiki/Evangelical_Lutheran_Church_in_America","//en.wiktionary.org/wiki/congregation","#cite_note-1","http://www.montanasynod.org/","/wiki/Synod#Lutheran_usage","/wiki/Diocese","/wiki/Evangelical_Lutheran_Church_in_America","/wiki/Montana","/wiki/Wyoming","/wiki/The_Reverend","/wiki/Bishop","/wiki/At-large","/wiki/Lutheran","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Evangelical_Lutheran_Church_in_Southern_Africa","#cite_note-3","/w/index.php?title=Montana_Synod_(ELCA)&action=edit&section=1","http://www.montanasynod.org/","/w/index.php?title=Montana_Synod_(ELCA)&action=edit&section=2","#cite_ref-1","http://www.elca.org/ScriptLib/CO/ELCA_News/encArticleList.asp?article=3605","#cite_ref-2","http://www.montanasynod.org/AboutUs.html","#cite_re